      "span_text": "Actinorhizal nodules are considered as modified lateral roots because (1) they originate from divisions in the pericycle in front of a xylem pole; (2) they have a lateral root-like structure with a central vasculature, infected cells in the cortex, and an apical meristem; and (3) in some species (e.g. Casuarina sp.) a so-called nodule root is produced at the apex [CITATION_4] ."
